lefExtend2DCellShapes(25.10)                      lefExtend2DCellShapes(25.10)

Name
       lefExtend2DCellShapes

Syntax
        lefExtend2DCellShapes { {layer extension_amount}... }

       Type: String

       Default: ""

       Specifies  a  list  of  layer and a value for creating obs shape for 2D
       pin/obs shapes. Cells could have 2D objects, which require larger line-
       end spacing. You can use  lefExtend2DCellShapes  to  automatically  add
       SPACING 0 OBS  for routing during LEF in..

       For  any  2D shapes, you can extend edges that are perpendicular to the
       preferred routing direction of the rectilinear shape by specifying  the
       extension_amount in lefExtend2DCellShapes.

       Note: Cells would still require explicit edge constraint to prevent im-
       proper cell abutment.

Example
       set lefExtend2DCellShapes {M1 0.1}

       The direction of M1 is Vertical.

